  "description": "This experiment focuses on configuring different permissions for development, testing, and operations personnel to operate different pipelines, and to manage the pipelines in groups. Users need to install the Role-based Authorization plugin and configure the authorization policy. Users can create roles and assign permissions to them as follows: View role for global roles, Read and Create Permission for Ops role, Dev role starting with dev- and Test role starting with test- for item roles. Finally, the experiment shows how to authorize individual users such as granting global view and project-based roles for zhangsan and lisi, and global ops role for joker.",
